article.description: Utah Valley State 70, Johnson and Wales (Den) 42
article.headline: Utah Valley State 70, Johnson and Wales (Den) 42
article.linkText: Utah Valley State 70, Johnson and Wales (Den) 42
article.story: OREM, Utah (AP) -- Junior guard Chris Bailey came off the bench Saturday to score 15 points and lead Utah Valley State to a 70-42 win over visiting Johnson & Wales of Colorado. Big runs at the beginning of each half propelled the Wolverines to victory. Utah Valley (14-12) raced out to a 14-0 lead at the outset, holding the Wildcats scoreless for the first 10 minutes of play. Johnson & Wales (1-25) was similarly lethargic at the beginning of the second half, watching the Wolverines put up eight quick points before a Wildcat shot even hit the rim. UVSC forward David Heck finished with 12 points, eight rebounds, and five blocked shots. Senior center Ben Devoe added 10 points for the Wolverines. Eric Daniels scored 17 points for the Wildcats. Utah Valley State shot 56 percent from the field while holding Johnson & Wales to a 26 percent mark. The Wolverines led 32-16 at halftime. Bailey scored 13 of his 15 points in the second half. Midway through the second half, Bailey scored five consecutive points on a 3-pointer from the top of the key and a fast break layup to put UVSC ahead 51-22. Later in the second half, Bailey scored eight straight Wolverine points. After sinking six free throws, Bailey's layup with four minutes left in the game gave UVSC its biggest lead of the night at 63-33.
